:R-HSA-73728  a             owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0006361 ;
        rdfs:comment        "The activity of the upstream binding factor (UBF-1) plays an important role in the regulation of rRNA synthesis. Studies reveal that phosphorylation of UBF-1 is required for its interaction with the RNA polymerase I complex, suggesting that phosphorylation of UBF-1 bound to the rDNA promoter during promoter opening modulates the assembly of the transcription initiation complex." ;
        rdfs:label          "RNA Polymerase I Promoter Opening" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: Gillespie, ME, 0000-00-00 00:00:00" , "Authored: Comai, L, 2003-07-03 17:13:29" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
